Wash and dry all produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from
greens.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp}(or 2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a small #pot over medium-high heat. Add
scallion whites; cook, stirring, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{3/4%cup} to coat, then add 1¼ cups water (2¼ cups for 4). Bring to a
boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, finely dice @roma tomato{1}. Peel and finely dice @kiwi{1}. Zest and quarter
@lime{1}.

In a medium #bowl, combine scallion greens, tomato, kiwi, and a big squeeze of lime juice
to taste. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Chipotle Lime Crema ==

In a small #bowl, combine @sour cream{4%tbsp}, lime zest, and a pinch of @chipotle chili
powder{1%tsp} to taste. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling
consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Like things spicy? Add more chipotle powder!

== Chicken ==

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%oz}(or 4 servings adjust accordingly) dry with #paper towels.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a large #pan over medium-high heat. Add
chicken, @Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}, and a pinch of chipotle powder if you like things
spicy. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1}, 2 TBSP water (or 3 TBSP water for 4 servings), and
a big pinch of salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until liquid has reduced and chicken is
coated and cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork; season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between bowls and top with chicken and salsa. Drizzle with crema and serve
with any remaining lime wedges on the side.